  {"a":"hwei_sup","b":"zyra","win":["Zyra","Zyra","Zyra","Skill","Hwei","Hwei","Hwei"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Zyra spikes hard at 2: she seeds plants and combos E (Grasping Roots) into Q (Deadly Spines) for a rooted, plant-amplified burst that outdamages your slow-forming spells. Her plants add sustained DPS to every trade, so respect the level-2 all-in and don't walk up into her seed range without a ward."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Zyra's R (Stranglethorn) is a delayed AoE knockup that pairs with her E root for a huge 2v2 combo, but it telegraphs; when she commits R you can sidestep and answer with your own R zone plus EE stun. This is where your poke war swings back as your combos come online."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Malignance and a lost-chapter item your burst combo out-trades her plant poke in mid-range, and you have cleaner all-in kill pressure. Kill her plants with a passing spell or just outrange the seeds, then blow her up while her E root is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"In 2v2 skirmishes Zyra is immobile with no escape; land your W root or EE stun and she dies before her plants and R can zone you. Your AoE control overtakes her plant-dependent damage once you have items."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive her level 1-3 plant poke and reach your level 6 spike","Sidestep her E root and R knockup then punish the immobility","Outrange or clear her seeds so plants can't stack chip on you"],"foe":["Stack plant poke and E-Q combos levels 1-3 before your R","Land E root into plant burst for a level-2/3 all-in","Zone your ADC off CS with seeded lane control"]},"early":"Zyra beats you levels 1-3: her E-Q plant combo roots and bursts harder than your telegraphed EE, and her seeds add constant DPS that zones your ADC off CS. Dodge her E root by staying spread, don't step on fresh seeds, and farm safe under tower while her mana is high.","mid":"Lane is Zyra-favoured until 6 (Skill at 4-5): trade only when her E root is on cooldown, since without it she can't lock you for the plant burst. Use W's shield/heal to sustain her chip and bank levels toward your spike.","late":"With your first item your mid-range burst and all-in threat overtake her plant poke; in 2v2 all-ins she's immobile, so your EE stun or W root lands and she's deleted before her R knockup and plants can zone you back.","whys":["Zyra's E-Q plant combo roots and bursts harder than your slow spells, owning turn one","At 2 her plant-amplified all-in outdamages your telegraphed poke","Level 3 her seeds add constant DPS and zone your ADC off CS","By 4-5 it evens as you bank levels and dodge her root from under tower","Level 6 your R and EE stun punish her committed, telegraphed Stranglethorn","Your first-item burst out-trades her plant poke with cleaner kill pressure","In 2v2 immobile Zyra gets deleted by your W root and AoE stun"]}
